title: Resource Constrained U-Net for Extraction of Retinal Vascular Trees
abstract:
This paper demonstrates the efficacy of a modified U-Net structure for the
extraction of vascular tree masks for human fundus photographs. On limited
compute resources and training data, the proposed model only slightly
underperforms when compared to state of the art methods.
subjects: Electrical Engineering and Systems Science/Image and Video Processing
